In [[telecommunication]], '''continuous operation''' is an operation in which certain components, such as nodes, [[telecommunications facility|facilities]], [[telecommunications circuit|circuits]], or equipment, are in an operational state at all times. Continuous operation usually requires that there be fully redundant configuration, or at least a sufficient ''X'' out of ''Y'' degree of [[Redundancy (engineering)|redundancy]] for compatible equipment, where ''X'' is the number of [[Spare part|spare]] components and ''Y'' is the number of operational components. 

