[[Image:Joint_Institute_for_Marine_Observations_logo.svg|right|thumb|The JIMO logo]] The '''Joint Institute for Marine Observations''' (JIMO) is a research institute that is sponsored jointly by [[National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration]] (NOAA)/[[Office of Oceanic and Atmospheric Research]] (OAR) and [[University of California|University of California's]] [[Scripps Institution of Oceanography]].
The JIMO research themes are: * Climate and Coastal Observations, Analysis, and Prediction Research * Biological Systems Research * Research in Extreme Environments * Research & Development on Observation Systems
